 "italic_en", "text": "of the Prophet"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was such as fitted close to the head,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not pointed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not going away into the air:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bTH", "text_ar": "بطح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalaAnisu", "text_ar": "قَلَانِسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalaAsK", "text_ar": "قَلَاسٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalaAniysu", "text_ar": "قَلَانِيسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalaAsiY~N", "text_ar": "قَلَاسِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalanosK", "text_ar": "قَلَنْسٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which last is [properly a coll. gen. n. of which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalanosuwapN", "text_ar": "قَلَنْسُوَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the n. un., being] originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalanosuwN", "text_ar": "قَلَنْسُوٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for there is no noun ending with an infirm letter preceded by a dammeh, wherefore the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and the dammeh into a kesreh, and then the word becomes like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaADK", "text_ar": "قَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaADiYN", "text_ar": "قَاضِىٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, K.) The dim. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qulayonisapN", "text_ar": "قُلَيْنِسَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qulayosiyapN", "text_ar": "قُلَيْسِيَةٌ", "orth_ty